This is a missed-optimization in GVN.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define void @test(ptr %p, i64 %v) {
entry:
  %tr = trunc nuw i64 %v to i1
  br i1 %tr, label %ret, label %store

store:                                            ; preds = %entry
  store i64 %v, ptr %p, align 4
  ret void

ret:                                              ; preds = %entry
  store i64 %v, ptr %p, align 4
  ret void
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define void @test(ptr %p, i64 %v) {
entry:
  %tr = trunc nuw i64 %v to i1
  br i1 %tr, label %ret, label %store

store:                                            ; preds = %entry
  store i64 0, ptr %p, align 4
  ret void

ret:                                              ; preds = %entry
  store i64 1, ptr %p, align 4
  ret void
}

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp:GVNPass::propagateEquality to implement the missed optimization:
```cpp
          if (MD)
            MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(NotCmp);
        }
      }
      // Ensure that any instruction in scope that gets the "A < B" value number
      // is replaced with false.
      // The leader table only tracks basic blocks, not edges. Only add to if we
      // have the simple case where the edge dominates the end.
      if (RootDominatesEnd)
